nz.co.jedsimson.lgp.core.environment

Interface EnvironmentFacade<TProgram,TOutput extends Output<TProgram>,TTarget extends Target<? extends TProgram>>

  • Type Parameters:
    TProgram -

    The data type of programs.

    TOutput -

    The output type of programs.

    TTarget -

    The target type of the dataset.

    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Environment

    public EnvironmentFacade<TProgram,TOutput extends Output<TProgram>,TTarget extends Target<? extends TProgram>>

    Acts as a facade for simplifying access to details of an class Environment.

    An class Environment is central during the operation of the system, as different sub-systems rely on it for providing random state, configuration, module instances, and numerous other things.

    This facade provides the public definition for an class Environment that consumers can rely on.

    See Also:
    class Environment, class Environment, class Environment
